        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 12:18PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 1217 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Stevenson, or 11 miles southwest of Bridgeport, moving southeast at
15 mph.

Pea size hail and winds in excess of 40 mph will be possible with
this storm.

Locations impacted include...
Henagar, Stevenson, Ider, Pisgah, Hammondville, Martintown, Rosalie,
Fabius, and Sulpher Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>Strong gusty winds will be capable of knocking down small tree limbs
along with other small unsecured items. Seek safe shelter until this
storm has passed.</instruction>
